org.factcenter.qilin.protocols.generic

Class BlumTwoPartyGroupElementFlip<G,C,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.factcenter.qilin.protocols.generic.BlumTwoPartyGroupElementFlip<G,C,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    G - Group element that will be returned from the flip
    C - Type of commitment
    R - Type of commitment's randomness
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TrapdoorBlumTwoPartyGroupElementFlip

    public class BlumTwoPartyGroupElementFlip<G,C,R>
extends java.lang.Object
    Use the Blum "coin-flip over the telephone" to randomly select a group element. Neither side (by itself) will know any additional side information about the selected element (e.g., the discrete log of the selected element will be hidden from both sides).
